Memory (RAM)

Definition:
-----------
Temporary / volatile memory
Used by system to perform tasks faster
Data is lost when the system shuts down


Purpose:
-----------
To hold running programs, active processes, and temporary data
Helps improve speed and multitasking

free -h          # Shows total, used & free memory (RAM + swap)
top              # Displays real-time memory usage of processes
htop             # (If installed) colorful, easier version of top
vmstat           # Virtual memory statistics
cat /proc/meminfo # Detailed memory info from kernel


ðŸ’¾ Storage (Disk / Hard Drive / SSD)

Definition:
Permanent / non-volatile memory
Used to store files, data, and system programs
Data remains even after shutdown


Purpose:
To store OS files, user data, and logs
Allows long-term saving and retrieval of information
Important Commands:

df -h            # Shows disk usage per filesystem
du -h            # Shows space usage of files & directories
lsblk            # Lists all storage devices & partitions
fdisk -l         # Shows detailed partition info
find / -type f -size +100M  # Finds large files



Feature	ðŸ§  Memory	ðŸ’¾ Storage
Type	Temporary	Permanent
Volatility	Volatile	Non-Volatile
Purpose	Speed & performance	Data storage
Example	RAM, Swap	Hard disk, SSD
Key Commands	free -h, top	df -h, du -h
